- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses lower and upper bounds on the tile complexity.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper uses geometric encoding for the digits of the counter.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the Tile Assembly Model has applications in the study of self-organizing systems and networks.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper uses the Window Movie Lemma and Catalan numbers in its analysis.
